The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Buddha on onion price
                                                                                                               Buddha on onion price
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee has expressed concern over the rise in the price of onion, finance minister Asim Kumar Dasgupta said at Writers Buildings on Friday. Bhattacharjee has said that he will write to the Union agriculture minister requesting him to organise a meeting with state governments to discuss the matter.        
	Pandal plea: Naba Yubak Sangha, which organises Fatakeshtos Kali puja off Keshub Sen Street, filed a petition before the high court on Friday seeking exemption from keeping 4ft free on all sides of their pandal. The matter is slated to come up for hearing on October 13.        
	Dupe charge: A complaint was lodged against Ramkrishna Dutta, behind bars for allegedly duping a student of Rs 3.5 lakh by promising him a seat in an engineering college, on Friday for taking Rs 6 lakh from a trader for admitting his son in a medical college.        
	Body found: The body of Sujit Pramanick, 25, was found in a pond at Sukh Pukur, under Calcutta Leather Complex police station, on Friday. He was allegedly strangled by his parents and dumped into the pond on Sunday.                                                                                                                                                                           
